popOnDrop is a dropbox addon that helps storing encrypted files to your dropbox account in cloud and helps decrypting the encrypted one and get notification on addition/updation of .txt or .doc file types and on deletion of any files.

popOnDrop works on linux powered using python.

System requirement:
Python 2.7+
PyQt4 (Indeed depends on SIP. Installation instructions can be found in "http://pyqt.sourceforge.net/Docs/PyQt4/installation.html")
Dropbox API (Installation instructions and downloads can be found in "https://www.dropbox.com/developers/core/sdks/python")

How to run?
>python popOnDrop.py

Notification on updation process is set to run even on closing of popOnDrop GUI to upload. This should be killed manually to stop.
